author: Coral Barry For Metro.Co.Uk
title: Arsenal news: Robert Lewandowski sends warning to Arsenal | Metro News
text:
Coral Barry for Metro.co.uk Sunday 12 Feb 2017 3:54 pm Robert Lewandowski has been in lethal form for his side (Picture: Getty) 
Robert Lewandowski has warned Arsenal Bayern Munich will be fully focused on their Champions League tie on Wednesday. Mesut Ozil suffering CRISIS of confidence, admits Arsenal boss Wenger 
Arsenal travel to Munich for the first leg of the last-16 clash hoping to end a long-running hoodoo against Bayern. 
The Gunners have never beaten Bayern over two legs with Arsenal having drawn the Bundesliga champions in each of the last four tournaments. 
Bayern have struggled to find the iron grip they usually command on the Bundeliga this season, but stay top of the table after a 2-0 win over Ingolstadt on Sunday. A photo posted by Robert Lewandowski (@_rl9) on Feb 12, 2017 at 6:50am PST 
Carlo Ancelotti’s side are now seven points clear of second placed RB Leipzig, but Lewandowski revealed the Champions League is Bayern’s main priority. 
‘The victory with Ingolstadt is already in the past,’ he said. 
‘Ahead of us is the most important part of the season – the Champions League is back.’ Bayern have managed to reestablish their grip on the Bundesliga in recent weeks (Picture: Getty)
